 ZHENGZHOU, Nov. 24 (Xinhua) -- The 600-year-old Forbidden City (Palace Museum) in the heart of Beijing is a cultural icon in China. Su Tangshi, a grassroots photographer in Henan Province, has been seeking to capture the beauty of the former imperial palace with his lens. In the past eight years, he went to the Forbidden City for nearly 80 times and snapped 300,000 photos of it.  Produced by Xinhua Global Service